      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-credibility-claim",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model credibly predicts absolute hemolysis index below clinical threshold for Class III VAD",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, when applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under VAD operating conditions (5 flow-speed combinations), produces absolute Hemolysis Index predictions that are credible for regulatory submission. Credibility is established through mesh convergence studies, turbulence model sensitivity analysis, and comparison against independent experimental datasets. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification demonstrates that 95th-percentile HI predictions remain below the absolute clinical threshold of 0.8 g/dL across all operating points. The model is deemed fit for purpose under ASME V&V 40 at Model Risk Level 5 for this Context of Use.",
      "scope": "Class III VAD; FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry; absolute HI prediction; MRL 5",
      "purpose": "Support regulatory submission to FDA demonstrating hemolysis safety of the VAD device based on CFD evidence"
    }
  ],
