    "rationale": "Despite seven credibility factors assessed below required levels and six factors not assessed, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis of the richly documented ValidationResults demonstrating GCI < 2.5%, Monte Carlo 95th-percentile HI = 0.61 g/dL below clinical threshold, and NRMSE of 14.3% within pragmatic bounds for MRL 5 submissions. The central hemolysis credibility claim appears well-supported by the validation evidence chain. Note: the bindsClaim node presents a comprehensive summary of model credibility that consolidates all validation findings; reviewers are directed to the ValidationResult nodes for primary evidence links.",
